text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia adinophylla is a shrub belonging to the genus Acacia and the subgenus Phyllodineae. It is native to a small area in the Goldfields region of Western Australia.The tangled shrub typically grows to a height of 0.3 to 1.6 metres (1 to 5 ft). It blooms from September to November and produces yellow flowers.
